      "words": 199,
      "text": "I used to believe that silence meant weakness. I thought the loudest people were the strongest, and that confidence had to be visible to be real. Growing up in a competitive environment, I often felt invisible when I chose to listen rather than speak. But as I grew older, I began to understand that strength can be quiet. The most influential people in my life were not the ones who talked the most; they were the ones who listened deeply, thought carefully, and acted with purpose. Silence, I learned, is not the absence of strength — it is often its most powerful form.",
