      "date": "15 Feb 2026",
      "words": 186,
      "text": "One important concern about using Artificial Intelligence in higher education is that students may start depending on it too much. AI is meant to support learning, but when it becomes the main source for doing assignments, it can slowly weaken important skills like critical thinking and problem solving. When students use AI to write essays or answer difficult questions, they miss the process of thinking deeply, questioning ideas, and building their own arguments. Critical thinking becomes weaker because it grows through practice and effort, not by receiving ready answers. In 2023, UNESCO warned that the uncontrolled use of generative AI in education could affect the development of essential cognitive skills.",
